📘 Subject: General Studies Paper I (Prelims – Polity)
🧠 Topic: Preamble of the Indian Constitution

(Very important topic for both Prelims and Mains.)

1️⃣ Core Teaching (Simple, Exam-Oriented)
🔹 What is the Preamble?

The Preamble is the introduction to the Constitution.
It explains:

Philosophy of the Constitution

Objectives of the Constitution

Nature of the Indian state

📌 It is often called the “Identity Card of the Constitution.”

🔵 Text of the Preamble (Key Words)

India is declared as:

Sovereign

Socialist

Secular

Democratic

Republic

These define the nature of the Indian state.

🔹 Objectives of the Constitution

The Preamble ensures:

1️⃣ Justice

Social justice

Economic justice

Political justice

2️⃣ Liberty

Thought

Expression

Belief

Faith

3️⃣ Equality

Equality of status

Equality of opportunity

4️⃣ Fraternity

Unity

Integrity of the nation

🔴 Important Amendments
42nd Constitutional Amendment (1976)

Added words:

Socialist

Secular

Integrity

📌 Very important UPSC question.

🔹 Key Constitutional Cases
Berubari Case (1960)

Supreme Court said Preamble is not part of Constitution

Kesavananda Bharati Case (1973)

Supreme Court ruled Preamble is part of Constitution

📌 Landmark judgement.

🔹 Importance of the Preamble

Guides interpretation of Constitution

Reflects goals of the nation

Shows values of democracy

